Much of the regulation in recent years has concentrated on improving the ship and its equipment. These proposals were looked at by the British government in the wake of the sinking of the Herald of Free Enterprise. Any review of ferry safety should focus on three main issues. Particularly worrying are the eyewitness reports which suggest that water penetrated the bow doors in a manner reminiscent of the sinking of the Herald of Free Enterprise in 1987. But the sinking of the Estonia should lead to a new review of ferry safety. 